#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:2769
msgid ""
"The red, green and blue components order code, as encoded in a pixel sample. "
"The possible values are shown in :ref:`bayer-patterns`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:2772
#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3875
msgid ""
"The number of bits per pixel component. All components are transferred on "
"the same number of bits. Common values are 8, 10 and 12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:2776
msgid ""
"The compression (optional). If the pixel components are ALAW- or DPCM-"
"compressed, a mention of the compression scheme and the number of bits per "
"compressed pixel component."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:2786
#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:8680
msgid ""
"For formats where the total number of bits per pixel is smaller than the "
"number of bus samples per pixel times the bus width, a padding value stating "
"if the bytes are padded in their most high order bits (PADHI) or low order "
"bits (PADLO)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:2795
msgid ""
"For instance, a format with uncompressed 10-bit Bayer components arranged in "
"a red, green, green, blue pattern transferred as 2 8-bit samples per pixel "
"with the least significant bits transferred first will be named "
"``MEDIA_BUS_FMT_SRGGB10_2X8_PADHI_LE``."
msgstr ""

