#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3860
msgid "Packed YUV Formats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3862
msgid ""
"Those data formats transfer pixel data as (possibly downsampled) Y, U and V "
"components. Some formats include dummy bits in some of their samples and are "
"collectively referred to as \"YDYC\" (Y-Dummy-Y-Chroma) formats. One cannot "
"rely on the values of these dummy bits as those are undefined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3868
msgid "The format code is made of the following information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3870
msgid ""
"The Y, U and V components order code, as transferred on the bus. Possible "
"values are YUYV, UYVY, YVYU and VYUY for formats with no dummy bit, and "
"YDYUYDYV, YDYVYDYU, YUYDYVYD and YVYDYUYD for YDYC formats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3879
msgid ""
"The number of bus samples per pixel. Pixels that are wider than the bus "
"width must be transferred in multiple samples. Common values are 0.5 "
"(encoded as 0_5; in this case two pixels are transferred per bus sample), 1, "
"1.5 (encoded as 1_5) and 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3884
msgid ""
"The bus width. When the bus width is larger than the number of bits per "
"pixel component, several components are packed in a single bus sample. The "
"components are ordered as specified by the order code, with components on "
"the left of the code transferred in the high order bits. Common values are 8 "
"and 16."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3890
msgid ""
"For instance, a format where pixels are encoded as 8-bit YUV values "
"downsampled to 4:2:2 and transferred as 2 8-bit bus samples per pixel in the "
"U, Y, V, Y order will be named ``MEDIA_BUS_FMT_UYVY8_2X8``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3894
msgid ""
":ref:`v4l2-mbus-pixelcode-yuv8` lists existing packed YUV formats and "
"describes the organization of each pixel data in each sample. When a format "
"pattern is split across multiple samples each of the samples in the pattern "
"is described."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3899
msgid ""
"The role of each bit transferred over the bus is identified by one of the "
"following codes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3902
msgid "y\\ :sub:`x` for luma component bit number x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3904
msgid "u\\ :sub:`x` for blue chroma component bit number x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3906
msgid "v\\ :sub:`x` for red chroma component bit number x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3908
msgid "a\\ :sub:`x` for alpha component bit number x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3910
msgid "for non-available bits (for positions higher than the bus width)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3912
msgid "d for dummy bits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3929
msgid "YUV Formats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/subdev-formats.rst:3975
msgid "MEDIA_BUS_FMT_Y8_1X8"
msgstr ""

